Inventory Management.Unnamed: 1: Create Cycle Count Task by Location
Inventory Management.Unnamed: 4: Make sure Cycle Count checkbox is checked for both Item and the Location that contains its stock units (Inventory).
Inventory Management.Unnamed: 5:
Using the location cycle count creation handheld process will create cycle count tasks for a specific location

Note: Be sure to delete and clear all entries in the CycleCountQueue, located within the Inventroy Admin tab BEOFRE TESTING.  When cycle counting via handheld "Perform Cycle Count" process, user will be prompted to count all specified items in the location.

Inventory Management.Unnamed: 4: Navigate to "Create Cycle Count By Location" under Inventory in handheld menu
Scan or enter the location to count
Optionally enter a priority for the cycle count. If no priority is entered, then the priority will default to five (Medium).
Cycle count tasks for the location will appear in the Cycle Count Queue table. (located in Inventory Admin menu option on the desktop UI)

Inventory Management.Unnamed: 1: Perform Cycle Count (with Item Image Display)
Inventory Management.Unnamed: 4: Select "Perform Cycle Count" button in handheld menu from Inventory
Inventory Management.Unnamed: 5:
1) After each item has been counted in a location, ** will appear left to the item number
2) If the correct quantity (according to Deposco) is entered, the task in CycleCountQueue will be changed to "Completed" status.  If a variance is detected, tasks will be generated in the "Manage Cycle Count Variances UI for a manager or supervisor to review.  More info on this in the next test script.

Inventory Management.Unnamed: 4: Scan or enter starting location (any location in the warehouse) and hit enter
User will be directed to the nearest location that has a cycle count task waiting to be executed
User will scan the location they're directed to
User will be shown a list box with items in location needing to be cycle counted.
User will scan SKU and hit enter

On the next screen, user will select the pack type and enter the quantity they counted. 
**User will see item image on this screen

If they enter the quantity that Deposco thinks is in the system, they'll be returned to the previous screen with the list of items to be counted. If they enter a different quantity, they will be asked to re-count and re-enter since a variance was detected.
User will be asked to re-count as many times as necessary until they either enter the same quantity twice in a row, or enter the quantity Deposco believes is in the system.
User will be returned to the item listbox screen to select another item at that location if necessary.  If not, they can select "Next Location" and repeat the process if there are more tasks

Inventory Management.Unnamed: 1: Manage Cycle Count Variances
Inventory Management.Unnamed: 4: User (typically a supervisor or manager) will enter the "Approve Variances" UI through a laptop or desktop
Inventory Management.Unnamed: 5:
Depending on which action was taken, stock units will be updated to reflect what was counted, remain the same and cycle count task will be complete, or remain the same but generate a new cycle count task for the same location. 

The process will be repeated until either there is no variance detected, or the variance is accepted in "manage cycle count variances".

Inventory Management.Unnamed: 4: A list of variances will be displayed.  A variance is any time a qty is entered that differs from what Deposco has listed in the system.
For each record you will see the item, counted qty, variance qty, reason code, and other relevant data. The columns listed can be adjusted.

Whoever is managing the variances can select the tasks and accept (stock units for that item/location will be updated based on what was counted), reject (stock unit for that location/item will remain with the same qty they had before the cycle count), or re-count (no change is made to the stock unit yet, and cycle count task is sent back to the floor to be re-counted).

Inventory Management.Unnamed: 1: On Demand Cycle Count
Inventory Management.Unnamed: 4: User will select "On Demand Location Cycle Count" from Inventory menu
Inventory Management.Unnamed: 5:
If the correct quantity (according to Deposco) is entered, the task in CycleCountQueue will be changed to "Completed" status.  If a variance is detected, tasks will be generated in the "Manage Cycle Count Variances UI for a manager or supervisor to review. (ref seq. 7)

Note: Be sure to delete and clear all entries in the CycleCountQueue, located within the Inventroy Admin tab BEOFRE TESTING.

Inventory Management.Unnamed: 4: User will be prompted to enter a location and priority (1-10 w/1 being highest priority). Priority defaults to 5 if left empty.
User creates cycle count task and will immediately begin task (reference seq. 3, steps 3.04-3.10) and will be assigned to the user to complete.

2) Non-controlled Physical Count Activity will be able to create and delete inventory. Stock units will be updated with whatever is counted for that location.
3) If controlled, discrepancies will be recorded in "Manage Cycle Count Variances" .

Inventory Management.Unnamed: 1: Replenishment Based on Open Orderline Quantity
Inventory Management.Unnamed: 4: Replenishments are generated on a scheduled basis for every location-item combination where current inventory levels for an item in a picking location is LESS than the the Open Orderlines for that item. The replenishment task will try to push the inventory level in the location to be enough to fulfill the open orders plus 20% more. All replenishments can be viewed in the "ReplenishmentTaskNew" entity
Set up test data to where there is an open orderline qty for an item that is greater than the quantity of that item in a pickable location. Ensure that the item exists in a Reserve location
Run the Open Orderline Replen Scheduler
Navigate to the Handheld-> Inventory-> Replenishments-> Directed Replen
Scan a container that is Type=Cart

User is taken to the "Pull Summary Screen" showing the Items, quantity, and location to replenish from. 
Select Next
The user will be taken to "Picking Screen" to scan and pick the item(s) to replenish
Step 1.05 will be repeated to complete all picks needed for all replenishment tasks (unless the user selects Exception or Cart is Full)
Once all picks are complete, the user is directed to "Replenishment Entry Screen" to replenish location with the picked items
User will scan the destination location, the SKU, and the replen quantity
Once all replenishment tasks are completed, the user will be taken to the main screen and will see the following message: "Nothing to replenish."

Packing.Unnamed: 4: Select Build Outbound Transfer Order from Store Operations menu
Packing.Unnamed: 5: 1)Ensure your user's Facility is set to the DPR or STPR facility. Screen should read 'Ship-To Facility'

Packing.Unnamed: 4: Enter the Ship-To Facility Number
Select a Transfer Purpose and scan the location with the stock to transfer
Scan the container user will be picking into
Scan the Items and on the next screen, enter the Quantity that user intends to transfer
User will be brought to a sumamry screen showing all items added to the Transfer Order. Confirm order by selecting "Next."Stage your container to a location
Packing.Unnamed: 5: User will see the following message: "Container (Container#) staged to (StagingLocation) for ship-to HZLHQ"

Packing.Unnamed: 4: Pack out the Transfer Order using the Transfer Order Packing button from the Store Operations menu
Scan the LPN label of the picking container, and select Next.
The Item Screen appears with a list of items in the container. Scan an item in container OR select the "Pack Remainder" button to pack out all items in the container
Select Cubed Packing from Outbound menu
Packing.Unnamed: 5:
1) Order's shipping status shows status "Shipped"
2) A shipment record is created for the order.
3) The picking container is updated to remove the stock unit that was packed. In addition, a shipping container is created as the item is packed.
4) A shipping label and packing slip is printed for the shipping container.

Packing.Unnamed: 4: Scan the LPN label of the picking container, and select Next.
The Item Screen appears with a list of items in the container. Scan an item in container.
Shipping label and packing list will print
User will be returned to the Scan Container Screen and see the following message: "Order [ ] has been successfully packed."
Select Single Scan Packing from Outbound menu
Packing.Unnamed: 5:
1) Order's shipping status shows status "Shipped"
2) A shipment record is created for the order.
3) The picking container is updated to remove the stock unit that was packed. In addition, a shipping container is created as the item is packed.
4) A shipping label and packing slip is printed for the shipping container.

Packing.Unnamed: 4: Scan the LPN label of the picking container, and select Next.
The Item Screen appears with a list of items in the container. Scan an item in container, then enter the quantity that will be packed on the next screen
Select the box from the Box list
Shipping label and packing list will print
If there are more items in the picking bin, then you are returned to the Item Screen to scan/select another item.
Select Outbound Transfer Packing from Outbound menu
Packing.Unnamed: 5:
1) Order's shipping status shows status "Shipped"
2) A shipment record is created for the order and an Inbound Transfer Order is created for the store to receive against

Packing.Unnamed: 4: Scan the LPN label of the picking container, and select Next.
The Item Screen appears with a list of items in the container. Scan an item in container or use the pack remainder button to pack out all items in the container
Packing list will print once all items are packed
User will then be brought back to the Scan Container screen
Select Bulk Packing from the Outbound Menu
Packing.Unnamed: 5:
User will see the following message at the end of packing:
[The request has been placed to ship orders.] Please check the notification center for error messages.

Weight will autopopulate, but select the carton type to pack the order out into
Select Ship All
User will be returned to the container entry screen
Select BOPIS Packing from Outbound Menu

1) Screen message should appear saying "Packing completed for order: [Order Number]."
2) Order's status shows status "Staged" and Order's shipping status shows "Not Shipped"

User will then be prompted with a list of items that are in said container.

User will be returned to the container entry screen
Navigate to "Move Container" under Inventory on handheld MainMenu
Packing.Unnamed: 5: Because BOPIS will be picked and packed through the main warehouse facility, and then moved to the store- this will be the next step. The order will be transported outside system. The "mover" will need to enter the device, and go to move container- where they will enter the container number and be given the option to change facility. Operator must change to destination facility, in order to receive product. From there, scan the location to drop off, and proceed to next step.
